1
00:00:49,640 --> 00:00:50,900
Mine is not bad either.

2
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:52,000
Sir, how about mine?

3
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:53,400
Not bad for the first time.

4
00:00:53,400 --> 00:00:54,260
Thank you, sir.

5
00:00:54,400 --> 00:00:55,480
Sir, look at mine.

6
00:00:55,480 --> 00:00:55,920
Average.

7
00:00:55,920 --> 00:00:57,200
You did a great job.

8
00:00:57,200 --> 00:00:57,960
Teach me later.

9
00:00:57,960 --> 00:00:58,480
Right?

10
00:00:59,600 --> 00:01:01,280
How did you do yours?

11
00:01:03,160 --> 00:01:03,680
Not bad.

12
00:01:04,120 --> 00:01:05,360
Sir, what's my level?

13
00:01:07,240 --> 00:01:08,600
If it were in the past,

14
00:01:08,760 --> 00:01:10,360
you'd be beheaded.

15
00:01:11,480 --> 00:01:13,210
Are you complimenting me, sir?

16
00:01:13,840 --> 00:01:14,360
Not bad.

17
00:01:15,800 --> 00:01:16,880
Let me see.

18
00:01:18,880 --> 00:01:20,160
Xiaocen's is good.

19
00:01:20,200 --> 00:01:21,880
It gave me a pleasant surprise.

20
00:01:21,880 --> 00:01:23,880
Smooth lines, elegant colors.

21
00:01:24,280 --> 00:01:24,800
Not bad.

22
00:01:25,480 --> 00:01:26,480
Thank you, sir.

23
00:01:27,400 --> 00:01:28,000
Professor.

24
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:29,080
Let me see.

25
00:01:30,440 --> 00:01:31,080
This is

26
00:01:32,160 --> 00:01:33,039
unqualified.

27
00:01:35,320 --> 00:01:36,240
May I know why?

28
00:01:38,160 --> 00:01:39,640
Look at it yourself.

29
00:01:40,320 --> 00:01:42,050
Yuan blue and white porcelain.

30
00:01:52,640 --> 00:01:53,280
Mr. Yue.

31
00:01:57,600 --> 00:01:58,200
Mr. Yue,

32
00:01:58,880 --> 00:02:00,740
can you stop speaking in riddles?

33
00:02:00,840 --> 00:02:02,970
Just tell me directly what I did wrong.

34
00:02:03,600 --> 00:02:04,400
Xu Xiao,

35
00:02:05,640 --> 00:02:07,440
have I ever spoken in riddles with you?

36
00:02:07,440 --> 00:02:08,880
I told you long ago.

37
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:10,530
Someone has a better

38
00:02:10,680 --> 00:02:12,840
understanding of blue and white porcelain than I do,

39
00:02:12,840 --> 00:02:13,720
and deeper.

40
00:02:14,440 --> 00:02:17,320
I took you all to the antique market.

41
00:02:17,720 --> 00:02:19,240
Why didn't you go see him?

42
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:21,920
Oh, you.

43
00:02:28,240 --> 00:02:30,600
Come have some tea, our great hero.

44
00:02:31,360 --> 00:02:32,120
Thank you.

45
00:02:34,240 --> 00:02:34,880
Xiao Xu,

46
00:02:36,480 --> 00:02:37,280
this weekend,

47
00:02:37,320 --> 00:02:39,960
Uncle Zhang is bringing two cups for appraisal.

48
00:02:39,960 --> 00:02:41,560
Could you take a look at them?

49
00:02:42,520 --> 00:02:43,120
Boss Wang,

50
00:02:43,720 --> 00:02:45,920
I want to take two days off this weekend.

51
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:46,880
Xu Xiao,

52
00:02:47,640 --> 00:02:49,800
are you going back to school this weekend?

53
00:02:49,800 --> 00:02:51,079
I happen to want to go to the library to borrow some books.

54
00:02:51,079 --> 00:02:51,680
No.

55
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:52,880
I...

56
00:02:54,360 --> 00:02:56,040
I've made plans with Wang Lin and the others

57
00:02:56,040 --> 00:02:57,240
to play ball outside.

58
00:02:59,640 --> 00:03:00,700
You all have plans.

59
00:03:02,840 --> 00:03:04,770
Then what should I do this weekend?

60
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:26,410
Hurry up. Come here.

61
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:26,840
Hurry up.

62
00:03:26,840 --> 00:03:27,480
Coming.

63
00:03:27,600 --> 00:03:28,200
Wang Lin.

64
00:03:28,360 --> 00:03:28,680
What?

65
00:03:28,680 --> 00:03:30,400
Are you going to the library this weekend?

66
00:03:30,400 --> 00:03:32,079
To find some info on firing porcelain.

67
00:03:32,079 --> 00:03:32,600
I'm not going.

68
00:03:32,600 --> 00:03:34,160
Li Zhuoting and I are going fishing.

69
00:03:34,160 --> 00:03:34,600
Fishing?

70
00:03:34,600 --> 00:03:35,640
How old are they?

71
00:03:35,680 --> 00:03:36,800
They're already acting like old men.

72
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:38,079
Bros for life.

73
00:03:38,200 --> 00:03:39,200
Wait for me a sec.

74
00:03:40,360 --> 00:03:41,160
Zhao Xiaocen.

75
00:03:42,640 --> 00:03:43,970
Wang Lin, what's wrong?

76
00:03:44,280 --> 00:03:46,800
The material Mr. Liang asked us to find last time,

77
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:48,079
you were the only one in the class who could find it.

78
00:03:48,079 --> 00:03:49,210
Where did you see it?

79
00:03:49,440 --> 00:03:51,320
I was in the rare book room

80
00:03:51,320 --> 00:03:53,520
between the third and fourth floors of the library.

81
00:03:53,520 --> 00:03:55,120
There are many rare single copies there.

82
00:03:55,120 --> 00:03:56,440
You can check them out there.

83
00:03:56,440 --> 00:03:58,840
Then call me next time you go to the library.

84
00:03:58,920 --> 00:03:59,640
Sure.

85
00:04:00,200 --> 00:04:00,960
Wang Lin,

86
00:04:01,320 --> 00:04:03,280
are you trying to extend your clutches

87
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:04,720
to Zhao Xiaocen now?

88
00:04:05,240 --> 00:04:06,500
You must be wary of him.

89
00:04:07,040 --> 00:04:07,960
What?

90
00:04:08,040 --> 00:04:09,640
Didn't Xiaocen help me handle

91
00:04:09,640 --> 00:04:11,080
the big teapot restoration issue last time?

92
00:04:11,080 --> 00:04:12,280
I have to show my appreciation.

93
00:04:12,280 --> 00:04:13,080
Revived! Revived!

94
00:04:13,080 --> 00:04:13,920
Come here quickly.

95
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:14,280
Okay.

96
00:04:15,320 --> 00:04:17,720
Aren't you going to play ball this weekend?

97
00:04:18,320 --> 00:04:19,279
I'm not playing ball.

98
00:04:19,279 --> 00:04:21,680
I made plans to go fishing with Li Zhuoting.

99
00:04:21,760 --> 00:04:22,160
This way,

100
00:04:22,160 --> 00:04:22,720
Zhao Xiaocen.

101
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:23,800
Keep up with me.

102
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:25,330
Let's grab a bite together.

103
00:04:25,400 --> 00:04:26,160
Sure.

104
00:04:26,680 --> 00:04:29,400
I'm starving. Why isn't it our turn yet?

105
00:04:29,880 --> 00:04:32,480
There should be three or four tables left.

106
00:04:33,920 --> 00:04:34,400
Wu Jing,

107
00:04:35,080 --> 00:04:36,940
ever since you rejected Wang Lin,

108
00:04:37,080 --> 00:04:38,880
I feel like he's taken a huge hit.

109
00:04:38,960 --> 00:04:40,960
I actually feel quite sorry for him now.

110
00:04:40,960 --> 00:04:42,360
What else could I do?

111
00:04:42,520 --> 00:04:43,840
I don't like him.

112
00:04:44,040 --> 00:04:46,880
Am I supposed to take responsibility for him?

113
00:04:47,240 --> 00:04:48,600
But who in high school

114
00:04:48,600 --> 00:04:50,320
didn't want to fall in love in college?

115
00:04:50,320 --> 00:04:51,650
You can date if you want.

116
00:04:51,680 --> 00:04:53,480
I'm going to wait and see anyway.

117
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:55,490
I'm telling you,

118
00:04:55,680 --> 00:04:56,760
if you keep waiting,

119
00:04:56,760 --> 00:04:58,880
the four years of college will pass by.

120
00:04:58,880 --> 00:05:00,280
If you don't take the initiative...

121
00:05:00,280 --> 00:05:01,240
Otherwise, later on,

122
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:02,480
it'll just be us lining up here,

123
00:05:02,480 --> 00:05:03,680
without a single man to save a spot for us.

124
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:04,480
Don't jinx it.

125
00:05:04,480 --> 00:05:06,080
How do I take the initiative?

126
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:07,880
It's simple.

127
00:05:08,560 --> 00:05:09,120
For the next class,

128
00:05:09,120 --> 00:05:11,320
didn't Mr. Yue say we can choose our own partners?

129
00:05:11,320 --> 00:05:12,560
Pick whoever

130
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:13,880
you like.

131
00:05:13,880 --> 00:05:14,740
Let me tell you,

132
00:05:14,920 --> 00:05:16,720
when two people spend enough time together,

133
00:05:16,720 --> 00:05:18,840
sparks will fly eventually.

134
00:05:18,840 --> 00:05:19,800
Look around carefully.

135
00:05:19,800 --> 00:05:20,400
Yeah.

136
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:22,840
Take Yuexin, for example.

137
00:05:22,840 --> 00:05:23,300
Yuexin,

138
00:05:23,640 --> 00:05:25,480
how about you team up with Xu Xiao next class?

139
00:05:25,480 --> 00:05:26,040
Yeah.

140
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:27,600
Xiaocen.

141
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:29,330
You might not know about

142
00:05:29,560 --> 00:05:31,000
Lin Yuexin and Xu Xiao.

143
00:05:32,400 --> 00:05:34,000
Since you don't share a dorm with us,

144
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,159
you don't know about this.

145
00:05:35,159 --> 00:05:37,620
Yuexin, don't treat Xiaocen as an outsider.

146
00:05:37,760 --> 00:05:39,800
Everyone knows you like Xu Xiao.

147
00:05:42,960 --> 00:05:45,040
Xiaocen, you didn't attend the military training.

148
00:05:45,040 --> 00:05:46,080
During the training,

149
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:47,800
the two of them took the punishment for us.

150
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:49,200
Right. Xiaocen, you really don't know.

151
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:51,760
Our whole dorm decided during the training

152
00:05:51,760 --> 00:05:54,159
that Xu Xiao and Lin Yuexin are the perfect match.

153
00:05:54,159 --> 00:05:55,600
Alright, stop talking.

154
00:05:55,680 --> 00:05:56,840
The military training was ages ago.

155
00:05:56,840 --> 00:05:59,040
Xiaocen, don't let them influence you.

156
00:06:00,280 --> 00:06:00,840
Xiaocen.

157
00:06:01,120 --> 00:06:03,380
I've been holding this in for a long time.

158
00:06:04,760 --> 00:06:05,440
Well.

159
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:07,920
Are you and Xu Xiao

160
00:06:08,800 --> 00:06:10,160
having a thing?

161
00:06:10,160 --> 00:06:11,920
Yeah, is there something going on?

162
00:06:11,920 --> 00:06:13,560
What do you mean by

163
00:06:13,760 --> 00:06:15,840
having a thing?

164
00:06:15,840 --> 00:06:16,600
Yeah.

165
00:06:17,040 --> 00:06:17,720
No.

166
00:06:17,720 --> 00:06:18,560
No, no.

167
00:06:18,560 --> 00:06:19,400
Is there?

168
00:06:19,400 --> 00:06:20,280
We are just

169
00:06:20,920 --> 00:06:21,680
friends.

170
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:23,530
Alright.

171
00:06:23,680 --> 00:06:24,880
Whether it's for business or personal.

172
00:06:24,880 --> 00:06:26,200
Shouldn't you let Lin Yuexin

173
00:06:26,200 --> 00:06:27,330
team up with Xu Xiao?

174
00:06:27,920 --> 00:06:29,000
Exactly. Yes.

175
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:31,400
It's settled then.

176
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:33,260
You don't like Xu Xiao, do you?

177
00:06:33,320 --> 00:06:34,200
Just to confirm.

178
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:35,680
Lin Yuexin likes Xu Xiao.

179
00:06:35,800 --> 00:06:36,800
And now you know it too.

180
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:38,840
So isn't it perfectly reasonable for them to team up?

181
00:06:38,840 --> 00:06:39,280
Right.

182
00:06:39,400 --> 00:06:39,800
Okay.

183
00:06:40,080 --> 00:06:41,280
It's settled then.

184
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:42,860
You two team up.

185
00:06:43,440 --> 00:06:44,300
You two team up.

186
00:06:44,880 --> 00:06:46,200
Medium table 37, are you here?

187
00:06:46,200 --> 00:06:46,880
Here, here.

188
00:06:46,880 --> 00:06:47,640
Time to eat.

189
00:06:47,800 --> 00:06:48,840
Let's go. I'm starving.

190
00:06:48,840 --> 00:06:49,840
Me too.

191
00:06:49,840 --> 00:06:50,900
Let's go, let's go.

192
00:07:02,400 --> 00:07:03,400
What are you doing,

193
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:04,400
sneaking around?

194
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:06,520
Sister, have you been well lately?

195
00:07:07,280 --> 00:07:08,320
Not bad.

196
00:07:08,960 --> 00:07:10,680
Why don't you ask me back?

197
00:07:10,920 --> 00:07:13,240
I'm so miserable.

198
00:07:14,640 --> 00:07:15,960
Have you finished your homework?

199
00:07:15,960 --> 00:07:18,120
I can't finish it. I just can't.

200
00:07:18,520 --> 00:07:20,680
The school already stopped giving us homework,

201
00:07:20,680 --> 00:07:21,880
but I don't know where Auntie

202
00:07:21,880 --> 00:07:23,160
got so many questions.

203
00:07:23,280 --> 00:07:24,920
She makes me do test papers as soon as I get home.

204
00:07:24,920 --> 00:07:26,520
Sister, do something

205
00:07:26,520 --> 00:07:28,680
to distract Auntie.

206
00:07:31,120 --> 00:07:34,000
Then I'll say I want to go shopping

207
00:07:34,040 --> 00:07:35,240
and ask Auntie to go with me.

208
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:35,760
Sister,

209
00:07:35,880 --> 00:07:37,600
you really can't lie.

210
00:07:37,960 --> 00:07:40,690
Auntie will probably see through you at a glance.

211
00:07:42,680 --> 00:07:44,240
I made plans with Wang Lin and the guys

212
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:45,360
to play ball outside this weekend.

213
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:46,240
I don't play ball.

214
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:48,520
I arranged to go fishing with Li Zhuoting.

215
00:07:48,520 --> 00:07:49,200
Xiaoxing.

216
00:07:51,080 --> 00:07:51,960
If...

217
00:07:52,640 --> 00:07:54,040
I mean, hypothetically,

218
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:58,680
if someone lied to you,

219
00:07:58,880 --> 00:07:59,800
why would they do it?

220
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:01,730
Well, it depends on the situation.

221
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:02,920
Take me for example.

222
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:04,240
Because there's this annoying guy

223
00:08:04,240 --> 00:08:05,400
who always asks me to hang out,

224
00:08:05,400 --> 00:08:06,200
so I lied to him

225
00:08:06,640 --> 00:08:08,770
and said I had to do test papers at home.

226
00:08:13,520 --> 00:08:14,000
Sister.

227
00:08:14,280 --> 00:08:15,140
Who lied to you?

228
00:08:15,320 --> 00:08:17,440
Which blind fool tricked you into what?

229
00:08:17,440 --> 00:08:18,080
No one.

230
00:08:19,640 --> 00:08:20,320
I know.

231
00:08:20,640 --> 00:08:22,520
It's the boy who walked you home that day.

232
00:08:22,520 --> 00:08:23,760
I know. It's him.

233
00:08:24,560 --> 00:08:25,880
Don't talk nonsense.

234
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:27,520
Sister, you dare to hide it from Auntie

235
00:08:27,520 --> 00:08:28,640
and date someone secretly.

236
00:08:28,640 --> 00:08:29,840
If Auntie finds out,

237
00:08:29,840 --> 00:08:31,320
she will skin you alive.

238
00:08:31,400 --> 00:08:33,240
I'll teach you a lesson for talking nonsense!

239
00:08:33,240 --> 00:08:34,840
Xiaoxing, Xiaoxing.

240
00:08:35,159 --> 00:08:36,080
Where are you?

241
00:08:37,080 --> 00:08:38,440
He's in my room.

242
00:08:38,440 --> 00:08:39,440
Here, Mom.

243
00:08:40,559 --> 00:08:41,220
Hitting me?

244
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:42,080
How dare you hit me!

245
00:08:42,080 --> 00:08:43,280
Come out and do your homework right now.

246
00:08:43,280 --> 00:08:43,880
Got it.

247
00:08:55,040 --> 00:08:56,570
Is there something going on

248
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:58,600
between you and Xu Xiao?

249
00:09:05,280 --> 00:09:06,340
I'm her classmate.

250
00:09:06,360 --> 00:09:07,320
My name is Xu Xiao.

251
00:09:07,320 --> 00:09:08,200
It's too late today.

252
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:09,400
So I brought her back.

253
00:09:18,280 --> 00:09:20,200
How do I really feel

254
00:09:20,800 --> 00:09:22,480
about Xu Xiao?

255
00:09:26,160 --> 00:09:27,800
Follow Mr. Zhou, everyone.

256
00:09:28,120 --> 00:09:28,650
Let's go.

257
00:09:30,760 --> 00:09:31,360
Xiaoxing.

258
00:09:31,560 --> 00:09:32,800
You can't run around today.

259
00:09:32,800 --> 00:09:34,530
I'm keeping an eye on you today.

260
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:36,660
Let's go. Follow Mr. Zhou.

261
00:09:37,160 --> 00:09:38,160
Come on, let's go.

262
00:09:40,120 --> 00:09:41,640
Children, take a look.

263
00:09:41,800 --> 00:09:43,040
Which ones are porcelain?

264
00:09:43,040 --> 00:09:44,760
Xiaoxing, does this look pretty?

265
00:09:44,760 --> 00:09:45,240
I don't want to look.

266
00:09:45,240 --> 00:09:47,040
Do you remember what I taught you

267
00:09:47,080 --> 00:09:48,760
about what porcelain looks like?

268
00:09:48,760 --> 00:09:49,680
Smooth.

269
00:09:50,320 --> 00:09:52,320
What else besides a smooth surface?

270
00:09:52,360 --> 00:09:53,600
And a lid.

271
00:09:53,640 --> 00:09:54,640
Brother-in-law.

272
00:09:55,080 --> 00:09:56,240
But some don't.

273
00:09:56,440 --> 00:09:57,080
Right?

274
00:10:10,640 --> 00:10:11,200
Sister.

275
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:12,600
Guess who I saw.

276
00:10:16,360 --> 00:10:17,040
Who?

277
00:10:38,440 --> 00:10:39,680
Don't follow him.

278
00:10:39,680 --> 00:10:40,640
Come back here.

279
00:10:56,520 --> 00:10:58,600
He sneaked into a room mysteriously.

280
00:10:59,400 --> 00:11:00,920
Sister, I'll keep an eye on him for you.

281
00:11:00,920 --> 00:11:02,600
I won't leave until he comes out.

282
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:04,600
Xiaoxing, don't be so nosy.

283
00:11:25,760 --> 00:11:26,200
Dad.

284
00:11:31,560 --> 00:11:32,280
Xiao.

285
00:11:38,240 --> 00:11:38,840
You.

286
00:11:42,800 --> 00:11:43,800
Why are you here?

287
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:47,760
Come.

288
00:11:47,840 --> 00:11:48,920
Come in.

289
